WEBVTT

00:00.227 --> 00:03.092
02x05 - <i>Nightmare on Lunch Box Street</i>

00:05.000 --> 00:11.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

00:12.837 --> 00:15.938
Ah, I see you moved my desk
over by the window.

00:15.978 --> 00:17.878
Great. Now if I want to jump out,

00:17.913 --> 00:19.780
I don't have that long walk
across the office

00:19.815 --> 00:21.515
to change my mind.

00:23.566 --> 00:24.909
Yeah, I just thought

00:24.934 --> 00:26.320
for, you know, the time being,

00:26.355 --> 00:28.081
it'd be better if we don't
look at each other,

00:28.106 --> 00:30.613
you know, because of your lying eyes.

00:32.900 --> 00:35.266
I want you to know that
this is killing me, all right?

00:35.302 --> 00:37.736
I've been crying for the last 24 hours.

00:37.771 --> 00:39.923
Every time I think about
what I did, I feel sick.

00:40.049 --> 00:42.116
Oh, hey, look, I know
this is hard on you, too.

00:42.184 --> 00:43.985
Can I get you a cup of tea, an aspirin,

00:44.053 --> 00:47.470
maybe somebody to sleep with
behind my back?

00:50.026 --> 00:52.059
Tea sounds nice.

00:52.094 --> 00:54.128
I am not getting you tea!

00:55.865 --> 00:57.832
Look, this is really hard.

00:57.867 --> 00:59.934
I-I just don't know
what I'm supposed to do

01:00.003 --> 01:01.035
to make things better.

01:01.070 --> 01:02.469
You can't, okay?

01:02.505 --> 01:05.038
So, let's just focus on the work.

01:05.072 --> 01:07.340
- Great.
- Okay.

01:07.375 --> 01:10.243
Here. This needs to be rewritten.

01:10.278 --> 01:12.328
Wait. I turned this in last week.

01:12.353 --> 01:13.369
You said it was fine.

01:13.415 --> 01:14.544
Yeah, that was last week.

01:14.573 --> 01:16.226
But now it's lacking honesty, truth,

01:16.251 --> 01:18.818
integrity, morality, loyalty.

01:20.488 --> 01:22.956
All right, I think we have
two options here...

01:22.991 --> 01:24.791
you can either beat up on me all day

01:24.826 --> 01:26.626
or we can get some work done.

01:26.662 --> 01:29.429
Ooh, I'm an excellent multitasker.

01:32.868 --> 01:34.400
I'll just quit.

01:34.436 --> 01:35.565
Hey, you know what?

01:35.590 --> 01:39.104
I thought I was handling this
pretty well, okay?

01:39.173 --> 01:41.139
This guy... he got cheated on,

01:41.175 --> 01:43.976
threw his wife's prosthetic leg
in the Chicago River.

01:46.080 --> 01:47.947
Sure, but if you read further,

01:47.982 --> 01:49.782
you'll see that he forgave her,

01:49.850 --> 01:52.985
and now they're currently out
shopping for a new leg.

01:58.025 --> 01:59.524
Oh!

01:59.560 --> 02:01.060
Guess what I just saw!

02:01.095 --> 02:04.196
Better not be another baby
dressed as a Chicago dog.

02:05.532 --> 02:07.399
- This was a lot of work.
- Ohh.

02:07.434 --> 02:10.401
There's so much stuff on it,
you can barely taste the baby.

02:10.437 --> 02:11.369
Aww.

02:11.438 --> 02:13.171
No, I was walking past

02:13.207 --> 02:15.173
the Chinese place
that used to be the Lunch Box,

02:15.209 --> 02:17.142
and I saw a "for lease" sign
in the window.

02:17.177 --> 02:19.377
They're going out of business!

02:19.446 --> 02:21.179
Well, I'm happy you're finding joy

02:21.248 --> 02:23.915
in the fact that a nice family's dreams
have been crushed.

02:23.942 --> 02:26.463
Boy, did you need a win.

02:26.588 --> 02:29.687
The point is, the Lunch Box
is for lease.

02:29.723 --> 02:32.757
I mean, those were
the best years of my life.

02:32.792 --> 02:36.161
Would it be crazy to open it up again?

02:36.196 --> 02:37.996
Are you really considering that?

02:38.064 --> 02:39.163
Yeah, I've been searching for something

02:39.198 --> 02:40.444
that's gonna make me happy,

02:40.469 --> 02:42.313
and... bam! I saw the "for lease" sign,

02:42.367 --> 02:43.379
and it hit me.

02:43.430 --> 02:45.903
I've been looking
to the future for answers,

02:45.939 --> 02:49.206
but all my happiness is behind me.

02:51.310 --> 02:53.477
We all thought you knew.

02:55.248 --> 02:56.748
And it came to me

02:56.783 --> 02:58.883
that you've got all this
restaurant experience now,

02:58.918 --> 03:00.417
so you could help me run it.

03:00.453 --> 03:01.385
Seriously?

03:01.420 --> 03:03.420
Yeah. We would get
the whole family involved.

03:03.489 --> 03:06.024
That's what made it
so wonderful to begin with.

03:06.059 --> 03:08.259
We all got together,
and we had one purpose...

03:08.294 --> 03:11.194
to make Roseanne happy.

03:13.999 --> 03:17.600
And now it would be to make me happy.

03:18.871 --> 03:21.304
If it works, I could be my own boss.

03:21.339 --> 03:23.273
That would make things so much easier.

03:23.308 --> 03:25.408
You could bring Little Bev to work.

03:25.443 --> 03:27.110
Oh, my God, we could put her
on the hostess stand

03:27.146 --> 03:28.779
and make her the hostess.

03:30.661 --> 03:32.620
When a baby says
there's a 20-minute wait,

03:32.645 --> 03:34.060
you don't get mad. It's a baby.

03:36.221 --> 03:37.988
They'll be lined up around the block,

03:38.023 --> 03:41.423
everybody waiting to make me happy.

03:43.795 --> 03:45.728
You have enough money
to open a restaurant?

03:45.763 --> 03:47.429
Yeah, I got a chunk put away.

03:47.464 --> 03:49.165
I made a lot as a trucker,

03:49.200 --> 03:51.433
and then there's the money
I got from that settlement

03:51.468 --> 03:54.303
when my boob got stuck
in that elevator door.

03:56.908 --> 04:00.609
Well, we'll do
a deep dive on that later.

04:00.644 --> 04:03.112
Uh, but if I hear you correctly,

04:03.181 --> 04:04.589
you're gonna be putting in all the money

04:04.614 --> 04:06.481
- and taking all the risk.
- I am.

04:06.550 --> 04:08.302
- Well, I'm in!
- Oh! Good!

04:09.700 --> 04:11.965
- Aaaah!
- Whoo!

